<br>
I'd say the best way would be that just take any normal night when we get 10+ people on, to recall and get out the alts if need be (or uncert something for the day) and grab reavers and head somewhere.<br>
<br>
We don't just have to pick one night.<br>
<br>
That's my idea.<br>
<br>
Here's what I recommend for all reaver pilots tho: bind at a tech plant nearby. They are the easiest to get to the reaver pad (and safer than running outside).<br>
<br>
So if you want to try this tonight or any other night, get yer alt into the outfit and we'll just do it.<br>
<br>
Also if you want to be really prepared, make a few favorites for reloading your reaver (if you survive that long <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
I have 3:<br>
all agile armor since that is all I have but since I change back to my regular load out before I fly (if I can), reinforced would make this easier:<br>
- 4 rocket packs (12 ea)<br>
- 3 rocket packs, 1 gun pack (100 rounds)<br>
- 1 rocket, 1 gun, 1 repair gun<br>
<br>
I keep my regular weapons in my holsters..in case I run into an enemy while reloading (it's happened!).<br>
<br>
The surge implant helps with reloading <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also note: when you run completely out of ammo and you load new ammo into the trunk...if you have time, jump into the reaver and Reload both ammo. Reloading the rockets is 24 rockets or 2 rocket packs that will be used up from the trunk. Then get out and run for another load of rockets.<br>
<br>
Other hints: <br>
<br>
Use the machine gun 97% of the time against other reavers/mosquitoes. Unless they are hovering or landed, rockets rarely hit. Machine guns are quite powerful. <br>
<br>
Use machine guns against moving vehicles 85% of the time. Only use rockets if they are stopped, about to stop (tree, etc) or you get really good at leading them with rockets.<br>
<br>
Use rockets against infantry and maxes 90% of the time. Be liberal with you use. You may run out of rockets faster but it's better to make sure they are dead than to take a rocket in the rear.<br>
<br>
Avoid the temptation to hover. Whether firing at an enemy or sitting around doing nothing...keep moving. You can set these things to orbit even while afk.<br>
<br>
While dogfighting and someone is on your 6, fly upwards not only by angling up but by using the E key, or down in combo with the C key. <br>
<br>
Always have afterburner juice before making a pass at a base/tower/enemy vehicles.<br>
<br>
I've rambled. Hope this helps a bit tho. Can't wait to try this.<br>
